      "content": "That's right, the escrow company acts as a neutral third-party holding the cash, ensuring that both parties fulfill their obligations. If the deal falls through, the escrow company will typically return the earnest money to you, minus any deductions for fees and charges. However, the process can be a bit more complicated if there are multiple parties involved or if the issue is related to the escrow company itself. It's not uncommon for escrow companies to have their own policies and procedures for handling refunds, so it's essential to review the terms of the escrow agreement carefully.",
